        <see>quantity on hand</see>
      </indexterm>Quantities on Hand by Item Group</title>

    <para id="Para616809">To view Quantities on Hand by Item Group, select the
    "Quantities on Hand by Item Group" option. The following screen will
    appear:</para>

    <para id="Para616813"><screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/IM_Disp_QOHByItemGrp.png"
                       id="Graphic616811" />
          </imageobject>

          <caption id="Caption616814">Quantities on Hand by Item
          Group</caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot></para>

    <para id="Para616815">When displaying Quantities on Hand by Item Group,
    you are presented with the following options:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616907">All Item Groups</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19417c8">
          <para>Select to display Quantities on Hand for all Item
          Groups.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616908">Selected</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947000">
          <para>Specify Item Group whose Quantities on Hand you want to
          display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616909">Pattern</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947048">
          <para>Enter an Item Group pattern to select a range of Item
          Groups.</para>

          <para id="Para677105">Refine your search using Regular Expressions,
          as described in <link endterm="Anchor77806" id="XRef677104"
          linkend="Anchor77806"> Pattern Matching with Regular
          Expressions</link>"Topic: Pattern Matching with Regular
          Expressions".</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para616917">All Warehouses</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x194706c">
          <para>Select to display Quantities on Hand by Item Group for all
          Warehouses.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry role="openmfg">
        <term id="Para616918">Selected</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947090">
          <para>Specify Warehouse whose Quantities on Hand by Item Group you
          want to display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616919">Order By</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19470d8">
          <para>Order the output by one of the following methods:</para>

          <para id="Para616920">Item Number: Select to order the display by
          Item Number.</para>

          <para id="Para616921">Value: Select to order the display by
          value.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616922">Show All Quantities</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947120">
          <para>Select to show all Quantities on Hand in the display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616923">Only Show Positive QOHs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947168">
          <para>Select to show only Inventory with a positive Quantity on Hand
          in the display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616924">Only Show Negative QOHs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19471b0">
          <para>Select to show only Inventory with a negative Quantity on Hand
          in the display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616925">Show Inventory Value</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19471f8">
          <para>Select to include the Inventory value of Quantities on Hand by
          Item Group in the display.</para>

          <para id="Para616926">Specify whether to display Inventory value
          using Standard Costs or Actual Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616927">Use Standard Costs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947240">
          <para>Select to show Inventory value based on Standard Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616928">Use Actual Costs</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947288">
          <para>Select to show Inventory value based on Actual Costs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616929">Quantities on Hand</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19472d0">
          <para>Display lists Quantities on Hand by Item Group, using the
          specified parameters.</para>

          <para id="Para675979">If the "Show Inventory Value" box is selected,
          the display will also show unit Cost, value, and non-netable value.
          Totals for each column will be calculated at the bottom of the
          display. If a Quantity on Hand value displays in the color orange,
          this means the actual or projected Quantity on Hand is at or below
          the Reorder Level. If the color is red, the current or projected
          Quantity on Hand is below 0.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para id="Para616931">To the far right of the screen, the following
    buttons are available:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616932">CLOSE</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x194733c">
          <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
          desktop.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616933">QUERY</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1947384">
          <para>Select to generate the display, using the specified
          parameters.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para616934">PRINT</term>

        <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x19473cc">
          <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

